description: Construction of four residential dwellings with associated parking, refuse storage, cycle storage and landscaping (following demolition of existing garages)
decision_conditions: The development permitted shall be begun before the expiration of three years from the date of this permission.

Reason: In order to comply with the provisions of the Town and Country Planning Act 1990 (as amended). | The development hereby approved shall be retained in accordance with drawing title number(s): 20007-CAL-XX-XX-DR-A-00000 Rev A Site Location Plan; 20007-CAL-XX-XX-DR-A-00001 Rev B Site Plan; 20007-CAL-XX-XX-DR-A-04000 Rev C Proposed Ground Floor Plan; 20007-CAL-XX-XX-DR-A-04001 Rev C Proposed First Floor Plan; 20007-CAL-XX-XX-DR-A-04002 Rev C Proposed Roof Plan; 20007-CAL-XX-XX-DR-A-05000 Rev B Proposed North Elevation; 20007-CAL-XX-XX-DR-A-05001 Rev B Proposed South Elevation; 20007-CAL-XX-XX-DR-A-05002 Proposed Street Elevation; 20007-CAL-XX-XX-DR-A-06000 Rev B Proposed Short Site Section; 20007-CAL-XX-XX-DR-A-06001 Rev B Proposed Long Site Section; 20007-CAL-XX-XX-DR-A-06100 Rev B Section A; 20007-CAL-XX-XX-DR-A-06101 Rev B Section B; 20007-CAL-XX-XX-DR-A-06102 Rev B Section C; 20007-CAL-XX-XX-DR-A-06103 Rev B Section D; 20007-CAL-XX-XX-DR-A-06104 Rev B Sec-tion E; 20007-CAL-XX-XX-DR-A-06105 Rev B Section F; 20007-CAL-XX-XX-DR-A-14000 Existing Site Plan; 20007-CAL-XX-XX-DR-A-14001 Existing Ground Floor Plan; 20007-CAL-XX-XX-DR-A-15000 Existing Short Section; 20007-CAL-XX-XX-DR-A-15001 Existing Long Section; 20007-CAL-XX-XX-DR-A-21000 Detailed Elevation; 20007-CAL-XX-XX-SH-A-ScheduleOfAccommodation Rev B Area Schedule; 20007-CAL-XX-XX-PP-A-DAS-(1 through 8 + 2 Addendums); Cover Letter prepared by DWD Property + Planning dated 8 July 2022; Daylight, Sunlight and Overshadowing Report prepared by OSM Chartered Surveyors dated 10 August 2021; Drainage Strategy Report prepared by Peter Dann Consulting Engineers dated November 2020; Landscape Sketchbook prepared by Jim Kelly Design; Preliminary Contamination Risk Assessment prepared by Paddock Geo Engineering dated November 2020; Statement of Community Involvement prepared by DWD Property + Planning dated February 2021; Transport Statement prepared by EAS dated 17 Febru-ary 2021.
Reason: For the avoidance of doubt, and in the interests of proper planning.

| Prior to the commencement of the development, all external materials (including brickwork, fenestration, boundary treatment, entrance gates etc.) to be used in the development shall be submitted to and approved by the local planning authority.

Reason: To ensure that the materials harmonise with the surroundings in accordance with the Council's adopted Ealing Development Management DPD (2013) policies 7.4, 7B and 7C, policies 1.1 (h), 1.2 (g) and 2.10 of the adopted Local Development Framework (Core Strategy 2012), policies D3, D4 and HC1 of the London Plan (2021). | The development shall comply with the relevant air quality neutral building emissions benchmarks for the residential development hereby approved.

Reason: In the interests of the internal environment of the development in accordance with policies 1.1(j) of the Ealing Core Strategy (2012), policy 7A of the Ealing Development Management Development Plan Document (2013), policy SI1 of the London Plan (2021), Appendix 5 of the Sustainable Design and Construction (2014) supplementary planning guidance, and the National Planning Policy Framework (2021). | Prior to the commencement of construction a detailed Demolition Method Statement Construction Management Plan shall be submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority. The management plan must refer to the following matters:
a. Removal of any earth from the site.
b. Site clearance, demolition, excavation and construction methods.
c. Site management and access.
d. Signage for construction traffic, pedestrians and other users of the site.
e. Prevention of mud and debris being deposited.
f. Vehicle and machinery specification.
g. Details of all Non-Road Mobile Machinery (NRMM) to be used on site.
h. Turning manoeuvres and routeing of vehicles.
i. Estimated number and frequency of vehicle deliveries.
j. Parking of construction vehicles.
k. Compliance with noise limits and vibration mitigation measures.
l. Procedures for on-site contractors to deal with complaints from local residents, liaison with local residents and notifications to interested parties.
m. Mitigation of air pollution and dust emissions during site clearance, demolition, excavation and construction works.
n. Waste management, hazardous material storage and removal.
o. Noise and vibration (according to Approved CoP BS 5228-1 and -2:2009+A1:2014)
p. Lighting ('Guidance Note 01/20 For The Reduction Of Obtrusive Light' by Institution of Lighting Professionals)
q. Hours of work and all associated activities audible beyond the site boundary restricted to 0800-1800hrs Monday-Fridays and 0800-1300hrs Saturdays.
r. Public display of contact details including accessible phone numbers for persons responsible for the site works for the duration of the works.

Reason: To protect the amenity of occupants and neighbouring properties in accordance with policy 7A and policy 7B of Ealing's Development Management DPD (2013), policy D14 and SI1 of the London Plan (2021), policy 1.1 (j) of the Ealing Development (Core) Strategy (2012) and National Planning Policy Framework (2021). | Cycle storage for eleven (11) bicycle spaces shall be provided within the curtilage of the site (as per drawing 20007-CAL-XX-XX-DR-A-0400 Rev C), within a secure, lockable compound in accordance with all adopted standards prior to occupation of the building and be continuously available and retained for the life of the development hereby approved.

Reason: To provide adequate bicycle storage to align with Sustainable Transport SPG and Policy T5 of the London Plan (2021). | The development hereby approved shall not be occupied until refuse and recycling storage has been provided, as indicated on the drawings / plans as listed in Condition (2), in accordance with the Local Planning Authority Standards and has been fully implemented and made available for use. These facilities shall thereafter be retained for use at all times.

Reason: To ensure the provision of satisfactory facilities for the storage of refuse and recycling material, in accordance with policies 1.1 and 1.2 of the Adopted Ealing Development (Core) Strategy (2012), policy 7B of the Ealing Development Management DPD (2013) and policies D3, SI7 and SI8 of the London Plan (2021). | The landscaping and private garden amenity area shown on the approved plan ref: 20007-CAL-XX-XX-DR-A-0400 Rev C and Landscape Plan Rev 03 dated 22.03.2022 shall be laid out and demarcated prior to first occupation of the units hereby permitted and retained in perpetuity thereafter.

Reason: To ensure that there is adequate provision of amenity space within the site in accordance with policy 7D of the Ealing Development Management Development Plan Document (2013). | The proposed rooflights hereby approved shall be Conservation Grade, shall not project more than 150mm from the roof plane and shall be obscure-glazed and retained as such for the lifetime of the development.

Reason: To minimise light spillage and interference with the privacy and outlook of adjoining occupiers and in the interests of good neighbourliness and in accordance with policies 7.4 & 7B of the Ealing Development Management Development Plan Document (2013). | No part of the flat roofs of the hereby approved development shall be used as or altered to form a balcony, roof terrace/garden or similar amenity area.

Reason: To protect the living conditions of occupants of nearby properties and future occupiers of the development, in accordance with policies 7A, 7B and 7D of the Ealing Development Management Plan (2013) and policy D6 of the London Plan (2021). | Notwithstanding the provisions of the Town and Country Planning (General Permitted Development) Order 2015 or any Order revoking and re-enacting that Order with or without modification, no extension, enlargement or other alteration of the dwellinghouse other than that expressly authorised by this permission shall be carried out without planning permission first obtained from the local planning authority.

Reason: The local planning authority considers that further development could cause detriment to the amenities of the occupiers of nearby properties or to the character of the area and for this reason would wish to control any future development to comply with section 7 of the National Planning Policy Framework (2021), policy 7B of the Ealing Development Management Development Plan 2013, policy 1.1 (g) of the Ealing Development (Core) Strategy 2012 and policies D3 and D6 of the London Plan (2021). | Water usage shall be restricted to a consumption of 105 litres or less per head per day (excluding allowance of up to five litres for external water consumption).

Reason: To ensure the development minimises the use of mains water in accordance with Policy SI5 of the London Plan (2021). | Prior to occupation of the use hereby approved, one (1) car parking space should be provided with Active Electrical Charging Points (EVCP) and the remaining two (2) car parking spaces should be provided with Passive Electrical Charging Points. The car parking shall be provided and managed for the life of the development.

Reason: To provide adequate facilities for drivers of electric cars, in accordance with Policy T6 of the London Plan 2021 and Ealing Development (Core) Strategy policy 1.1(h). | Prior to the commencement of the development, details regarding street lighting shall be submitted to and approved by the Local Planning Authority. These details include its location, design, materials, hours of operation, vertical illumination lux levels, glare and sky glow. External artificial lighting shall not exceed the vertical illuminance lux levels at neighbouring premises that are recommended for Environmental Zone 3 by the Institution of Lighting Professionals in the 'Guidance Note 01/20 For The Reduction Of Obstructive Light'. Glare and sky glow should be prevented by correctly using, locating, aiming and shielding luminaires, in accordance with the Guidance Note.

Reason: To safeguard neighbouring amenity from light pollution in accordance with policy 7B of Ealing's Development Management DPD. | Prior to first occupation of the development, a plan showing details of the green roof including species, planting density, substrate and a section at scale 1:20 showing that adequate depth is available in terms of the construction and long-term viability of the green roof, and a programme for an initial scheme of maintenance shall be submitted for written approval by the local planning authority. The green roof shall be provided in accordance with the approved details prior to occupation and thereafter retained and maintained in accordance with the approved scheme of maintenance.
Reason: To ensure the green roof is suitably designed and maintained in accordance Policies G1 and G5 of the London Plan (2021).
